5 1st off, Breakfast all day 24/7. Who doesn't love that! 2nd, The pies selection is fantastic. I found out that they come from the Market Street bakery in Sun Prairie. Hats off to them!!!!!  Burgers and dinner menu- Great home cooking! fresh well made food that gives mom's at home cooking a run for it's money!  "If you are hungry for a great filling meal, just head to Monty's" is my new Motto.   Love the huge parking lot! Easy in and out every time (if you can find a spot due to me being not the only other person loving this joint) Wish they had later hours. They are only open to 10pm, which I'm kind of confused with considering they are directly across from the Barrymore theater.  But...I still have a solid 5 stars for this new love of my life.
3 So when that BBQ Joint was randomly closed on a Friday night- we would up here.  I had not been here in a few years so forgot how vegetarian friendly this place is. If you are a vegetarian this place is great, but if you are meat eat- this place is also good.  They do comfort food in good portions at reasonable prices. The food is not spectacular, its not taking you back to Grandma's kitchen. But if you go here often- I can see it turning to the neighborhood joint, when you feel like home. You can bring your friends or family, and have a decent meal. But given I live across the city-that's not going to be me. So i judge it just purely based on the food, and on this particular day- it was as Yelp puts its "A-Ok."  I got the Bistro Burger with fries. It was cooked how I like it. My husband got the Roast Turkey Platter- it was really tender but a little bland for my taste. As Elizabeth said- the brocolli was good. The blanching makes a huge difference.The mashed potatoes decent. The service acceptable.   I would go back but it would not be my first choice.
4 It is absolutely what you want it to be. It embodies the era of diners so well. The food was delicious. I have had the Grilled Cheese and the Mac and Cheese (I added bacon, yum!) both were wonderful. The milkshakes and malts are amazing as well. It can definitely get loud and sometimes there's a wait, but either way it is definitely worth it for this Madison gem.
4 I always have awesome food here. I am ready to start tryign out awesome coctails
4 great diner with good veggie and vegan options. overall very nice staff, friendly, prompt great desserts!
5 Driving back from Wisconsin Dells to Illinois hungover and following a strict vegetarian diet, can be a little tricky. I hadn't been to Madison in a few years, so we decided to try a place in Madison (I also figured that they would be more likely  to have restaurants that cater to my needs). My boyfriend did some yelping, and shortly we were on our way to Monty's. There is a private lot which is always nice when you're in a busy city. We did not sit outside because it was a little chilly but the patio looked pleasant and relaxing with beautiful flowers. When you go inside the ambience is a funky little 50's diner with amazing looking pies. Even though the restaurant was crowded, we were able to get a table fairly quickly. As I opened up the menu, I almost died but before that I even thought of moving to Madison right away! There are so many vegetarian, vegan, gluten free options that it is the majority of the menu, which is so rare to find at a breakfast diner. We both ordered the sweet potato hash and it was to die for! Just what we needed that day! I wish there was another one in Illinois. My only suggestion is to serve the fruit on a separate plate instead of piling it all on one big plate, that makes the food messy and crowded.
3 I have a love/not love relationship with Monty's. I used to love them for b-fast when I ate omlets. Now that I'm vegan, it's kinda hard to love them. Many of the items can't be changed, so if you're not a fan of onions or even allergic to them, they can't come out of items because they are pre-made in batches. They are my last ditch place to go to if Lazy Jane's, The Green Owl or any other place is busy or closed.
4 Had to visit this place while in town based on a recommendation from a good friend. I had the sesame chicken salad and a brandy alexander to drink-- both tasted great...but wish I would have ordered the vegetarian meatloaf with cashew-ginger gravy, as I tasted my friend's and it was SPECTACULAR! Unlike anything I ever had-- I've been craving it since we were there. Cute/comfortable/casual atmosphere, polite and pleasant server, good/unique variety and great vegetarian options-- highly recommend this place if you're looking for comfort-type food and/or a place that feels low-key.
5 Came in for brunch today and had a very nice experience.  I really like their décor, classic diner style.  I got the Meatloaf and oh my goodness it was so AMAZING! The homemade gravy was to die for!  My friend got the Egg Mornay I didn't try it but it looked delicious.  Our server Eric was also amazing! I will definitely be returning soon, for a first time experience I give five stars!   As a side note as we were walking out every single employee that we passes said, "Thank you, have a great day."
4 I love this place! They have amazing cheesecakes, breakfast options and yummy sammies. My favorite thing to eat is the grilled chicken and goat cheese sandwich! The flavors are so fresh and work well. I also love to sneak raspberry cheesecake when I am done ;)
4 It's always fun to take people to Monty's. The parking lot is a good indicator of how busy the place will be. Be aware, though, that the booths have very little tummy room, especially for those of us who aren't so svelte. If you fall into that category, try to get a table on the left side of the restaurant. Your ego will thank me later. :-)
4 I could have sworn I wrote a review?  anyhoo...  went here on the suggestion of a few vegheads.  they used to have vegan milkshakes & ice cream... sadly, no more :(  dinner was tasty, though-- heathen vegan shoplifter sandwich & cherry pie!!! nothing Earth-shattering, but solid.   and probably one of your vegan best options in Madison.
4 This place has really great brunch.  They also serve alcohol (bottled beer and spirits only).  I had their Bloody Mary and an omlet last time I was there and it just felt right.  Try having that experience at a Perkins or Dennys.  Not happening. (P.S. the omlets are amazing, and if you ask for jalapenos on the side, they are fresh cut which rocks socks in my opinion)   Also, the place is very natural, with all of its ingredients seemingly sourced locally or something - the ingredients are fresh is what I mean to say.  Not even comparable to a Denny's, so don't let me above reference scare you.
